Name: abs_i - absolute value of integer 
 Synopsis:  integer abs -> integer

Examples:

-3 abs_i -> 3


Description:

implemented by C/C++ 
long   labs(long) and


Remarks:

If you are not sure, if the value is of type double or integer, use 
abs. If e.g. abs_d gets an integer as argument, NEST will exit throwing an 
assertion.


